array computing for postgres

pgtensor adds a tensor datatype to PostgreSQL.

Why?

To enable computing on multidimensional numerical data without having to round trip from a database to (e.g.) a Python script and then back to a database.


Roadmap:
- To/From Array
- Reshape (Transpose)
- Slicing
- Elementwise Operations
- Linear algebra primitives
- Slicing
- Broadcasting
- OpenBLAS integration
- Tiling (c.f. PostGIS ST_SUBDIVIDE)
- Expanded object form for efficient in-memory computation